<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About West Hillhurst</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Located in the inner suburbs of northwest quadrant of Calgary, Alberta, West Hillhurst is an executive residential community. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The southern border of West Hillhurst is marked by the Bow River, while 9th Avenue NW is towards the northern border. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The Crowchild runs through and bisects West Hillhurst community. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The western border is flanked by 28 Street NW, while to the east is 18a Street NW.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">The origins of the development of West Hillhurst real estate can be traced back to 1945 when “victory homes” were built for soldiers of World War II in the neighborhood. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">West Hillhurst homes for sale have an average asking price of $970,000, with a percentage of homes being $2 million or more. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Homes in West Hillhurst feature a delightfully eclectic mix of old and new.</p>
        </div>
